sort1 uses: Bubble Sort

How do you know?:

reversed50,000.txt -> 5.756s
sorted50,000.txt -> 0.644s

for sorted files, sort1 was the fastest in sorting them.


---
sort2 uses: Merge Sort

How do you know?:


reversed50,000.txt -> 0.459s

fro a revesed txt file of 50,000 numbers, it was exponenially faster compared to the other sorting programes.



---
sort3 uses: Selection Sort

How do you know?: 

reversed50,000.txt -> 4.021s
sorted50,000.txt -> 3.574s

It was the slowest sorting program in both a reversed numbr text file, as well as a sorted text file. Hence we can couclude thet this is selection sort.
